===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|こぶし|yomi=k}}
Probably from {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}.  First cited to a text from 810 {{CE}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Japanese dictionaries do not list any further derivation.<ref name="KDJ"/><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref><ref name="DJS">{{R:Daijisen}}</ref> A surface analysis suggests that this term might be a compound. If so, possibly from {{m|ja|小|tr=ko|pos=[[diminutive]] [[prefix]]}} + {{m|ja|節|tr=fushi||[[joint]]; [[knuckle]]; [[knob]]}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|こぶし|acc=0|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|こぶし}}

# {{defdate|from 810}} [[fist]]
# {{defdate|from early 1300s}} the [[shape]] of the [[hand]] when [[grip#Verb|gripping]] a [[sword]] [[hilt]]
# {{defdate|from early 1300s}} {{q|by extension}} [[swordsmanship]], [[ability]] with a [[sword]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|腕前|tr1=udemae|t1=[[ability]]}}
# {{defdate|from 1500s}} the [[shape]] of the [[hand]] when [[grip#Verb|gripping]] a [[bow]]
# {{defdate|from 1500s}} {{q|by extension}} [[bowmanship]], [[ability]] with a [[bow]]
